1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,600
Stop apologizing.

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:02,360
So you two become loving.

3
00:00:02,360 --> 00:00:05,560
I remember you two were always bickering.

4
00:00:05,720 --> 00:00:07,320
Why do you fall for a guy like me?

5
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:08,720
I just like you.

6
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:10,520
I don’t need a reason for it.

7
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:11,680
He kissed me.

8
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,000
I’m still thinking about what happened.

9
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,560
If you’re still thinking about it,
doesn’t it mean that you…

10
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:19,760
I’m not sure.

11
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,960
Did they tell you where they were going?

12
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:24,560
But if it bothers you, you should talk to them.

13
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,200
Do you want to have a meal with me?

14
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:27,560
Sure.

15
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,080
Do you want to come to my room
to play games?

16
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:40,600
(At one point in our life
when dreams are shining all over the sky.)

17
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:47,560
(We can’t even choose
which dream we should reach for.)

18
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:52,800
(Sometimes, you find your dream
in a boring class in school.)

19
00:00:56,320 --> 00:01:00,000
(Sometimes, you find your dream
from advice from your best friend.)

20
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:09,480
(When we have a dream,
we know that it’s not easy to achieve it.)

21
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,520
♪ When the sky clears after the storm ♪

22
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:17,480
♪ We start our journey together and move on ♪
(Many people give up along the way.)

23
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:20,360
♪ Every story we go through
turns into a memory ♪

24
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:21,880
♪ Every story we go through
turns into a memory ♪
(Many people achieve their dream.)

25
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:22,680
♪ That reminds us
how far we have come along ♪
(Many people achieve their dream.)

26
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:27,080
♪ That reminds us
how far we have come along ♪

27
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,200
(For someone,)

28
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,960
(They can only dream of it.)

29
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:44,240
Can’t you let me sleep a bit more?

30
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,040
Is he home?

31
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,600
Honey.

32
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:39,120
Will I get to eat breakfast today?

33
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,560
Stop teasing me.

34
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,040
Get your dad away from me.

35
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:43,720
Where do you want me to go?

36
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:45,480
Can’t you take the laundry out?

37
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,080
Why? Are you feeling shy
because of our son?

38
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,280
Go take the laundry out.

39
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:52,760
I miss you.

40
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:55,760
Why would you miss me?

41
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,920
Here is your rice.

42
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,240
Why won’t Dad have breakfast with me?

43
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,040
He already ate. You can go ahead and eat

44
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:08,840
Bummer

45
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,560
You woke up this late.

46
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,560
Are you expecting your dad and me
to wait for you?

47
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:13,800
Fine.

48
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,240
Mom.

49
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:24,800
Yes?

50
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,520
You called me,
and why didn’t you say anything?

51
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:38,600
When Dad tried to win your heart,
what did he do?

52
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:49,720
So my son wants to be in a relationship,
don’t you?

53
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:53,080
No, I’m just asking.

54
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,280
I don’t want to know anymore.

55
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,960
Your dad often patted me on my butt.

56
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,960
Huh? What do you mean?

57
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:00,960
Have you never heard this?

58
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,840
When you like someone,
you want to tease them

59
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,600
Can you stop joking?

60
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,120
You seem to be serious about it.

61
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:12,840
I guess you must want to be in a relationship.

62
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,280
No need to be shy.

63
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,680
You can tell me anything.

64
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,200
Ask me.

65
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:21,360
Why are you talking about me now?

66
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:25,800
Your dad did what other guys do
when they hit on a girl.

67
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,320
He took me out on a date
and went to see a movie.

68
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:29,680
He bought me my favorite food.

69
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,640
But friends also do that, don’t they

70
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,160
That’s nothing special about it.

71
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,400
Mister Romeo.

72
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,640
It hurts.

73
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:46,160
Yes, you can go to see a movie
or eat out with your friend.

74
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:51,680
But it’s different
when we go with someone we like.

75
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,040
How?

76
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,600
Of course, it’s different.

77
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,080
Otherwise, we wouldn’t call them
our special someone.

78
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,640
What do you mean
when you said it’s special?

79
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:08,200
I’ve never seen you have so many questions
when you ask me about your homework.

80
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:09,800
Mom.

81
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,840
You, little rascal.

82
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:16,720
I can’t explain the feelings to you.

83
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,480
You have to experience them yourself.

84
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:23,520
But I believe when that day comes,
you will know it.

85
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,640
Hey.

86
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,760
Why did you smack my butt?

87
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:37,840
You need to notice
if that person pats on your butt.

88
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,120
Aren’t you going to eat your breakfast?

89
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:47,080
No. I’m going back to bed.

90
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,080
Did he finish his breakfast?

91
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:50,120
No.

92
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:53,960
Honey, I think he’s dating someone.

93
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,880
Really?

94
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:07,080
Ko Song.

95
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,280
I need to give the food to my mom first.

96
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,160
Alright.

97
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:26,480
If I have feelings for him,
I hope an orange falls from the tree.

98
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:33,960
Come on. Fall down.

99
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:36,680
This is it.

100
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,080
Fall down.

101
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:40,040
It’s coming.

102
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:41,840
Come on.

103
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,240
Nothing.

104
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:49,440
Nothing.

105
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,080
It’s good that it doesn’t fall down.

106
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:07,760
Orange.

107
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:08,960
Yeah.

108
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:11,560
Ouch.

109
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,600
Ko Song.

110
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,280
I thought you would catch it.

111
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,240
I got a few for you.

112
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,600
Well done, Ko Song.

113
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,520
What’s going on?

114
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:37,720
What?

115
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:41,160
Why did you call me?

116
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,920
Nothing.

117
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,800
I just want to call you.

118
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,440
Really?

119
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,160
Yes.

120
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:55,000
Why? Can’t I call you?

121
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:57,840
It’s just strange.

122
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,040
How?

123
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:03,960
It’s odd.

124
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,400
Are you suspecting me?

125
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,200
How dare you?

126
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,320
Okay.

127
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:30,480
Ko Song.

128
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:31,000
Yeah.

129
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:34,720
I want to eat oranges again tomorrow.

130
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,240
I’ll bring them.

131
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,920
I want to eat dough sticks at the market, too.

132
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,320
I’ll go with you.

133
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,400
After that, I have to buy plants for my mom.

134
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:48,760
I’ll help you.

135
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:55,320
I also want to eat ice cream
at the shop near August’s house.

136
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:57,080
Sure.

137
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,160
We can ride our bike there.

138
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,200
I also want…

139
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:02,720
Orange.

140
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,640
I’ll do everything you ask me to do.

141
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:09,880
Okay?

142
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,160
Fine.

143
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,200
I got it.

144
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,840
Thank you, Achi, for buying us ice cream.

145
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,440
You can order more if you want.

146
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:53,360
Don’t give him ideas like that.

147
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,160
Too late. I’m milking it.

148
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:57,040
August, wait for me.

149
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:01,960
Ko Song.

150
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:02,520
Yeah.

151
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,400
When did you start to eat lime ice cream?

152
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,520
I want to try something new.

153
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:09,400
I can’t eat oranges every day like you.

154
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,920
Ko Neung, you really like oranges.

155
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,240
What would you do if you don’t get oranges
from Ko Song’s house?

156
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,720
I can’t help it. They are delicious.

157
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:26,400
You’re going all out
when Achi said it’s on him.

158
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,600
I’m holding back.

159
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:32,400
If I weren’t, I’d order five more.

160
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,080
Do you want more?

161
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,360
Stop it, Achi.

162
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:35,920
I’m asking you.

163
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:40,040
Achi, I’m just being sarcastic.

164
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,200
You are so naïve, little boy.

165
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:57,800
Achi.

166
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:02,280
Does your chauffeur have to wait for you here?

167
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:05,800
Yes.

168
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,800
My mom told him to wait to take me home.

169
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,640
Is he the Terminator?

170
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,480
No, he’s very kind-hearted.

171
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,280
It’s like he always keeps an eye on you.

172
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,680
It would be hard for you to date.

173
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,080
Only fools choke on ice cream

174
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:28,360
No, I got brain freeze.

175
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,640
Since it’s school break.

176
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:36,440
Do you want to take a trip and
stay at my mom’s beach house in Hua Hin?

177
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:39,120
Do you want to go?

178
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:48,120
You can say no. It’s okay.

179
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,840
Of course, we want to go.

180
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:55,080
Achi, you are taken aback, right?

181
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:56,920
Look at his face.

182
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,640
Of course, we will go.

183
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,240
What is this?

184
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,160
Ko Song, you also play along with them?

185
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,480
How can you do this to me?

186
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,480
I’m hanging out with them for too long.

187
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:10,760
Then…

188
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,680
Let’s say cheers

189
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:14,280
Sure.

190
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,920
Come on.

191
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,200
Come on.

192
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,560
One, two, three.

193
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,600
Yay!

194
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,400
We are going to Hua Hin tomorrow.

195
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,360
I know that.

196
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:30,120
That’s why we hurried back home to pack our bags.

197
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,400
It means that we won’t get to eat
dough sticks at the market

198
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,160
or buy plants for your mom.

199
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:38,320
We didn’t get to eat ice cream together.

200
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:39,920
We can do that after we get back.

201
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:44,200
The plants that we want to buy
will grow a little bigger.

202
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,040
What’s wrong?

203
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,720
A beach trip is more fun
than going to the market.

204
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,200
We will get to spend time together
when going to the market.

205
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,720
We will spend time together on the trip.

206
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,520
But it’s just the two of us
when going to the market.

207
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:06,640
I…

208
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,560
Follow me.

209
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:10,360
Huh?

210
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,120
Didn’t you say you want to spend time together?

211
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,320
I’m making up for it.

212
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:17,920
Do you want to do it or not?

213
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,400
If not, you can go home.

214
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,200
I’ll put my bike back at home.

215
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,280
Hurry back.

216
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,720
Ko, I want to eat oranges.

217
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,240
But you already ate them this morning.

218
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,360
Oh.

219
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,200
You are not only the big guy
in the neighborhood,

220
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:58,200
but you can also order the orange tree
to do what you want.

221
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:01,920
Yes, Boss Ko is the real deal.

222
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:03,160
Here.

223
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,560
My hands are busy. I’m holding the book.

224
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,080
One more.

225
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,200
- Feed me properly.
- Okay.

226
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:42,280
Is this a gate or a wall? Why is it so tall?

227
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,600
Ko Song, his house looks like a village.

228
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,720
Hold on, everyone.

229
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:50,760
Why?

230
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,400
Step closer.

231
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:53,960
Why?

232
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:54,920
I’m going to take a picture.

233
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:56,800
Right, take a picture. Come on.

234
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:57,760
Make a pose.

235
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:01,480
Ready? One, two, three.

236
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:05,160
You look good.

237
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,000
Wait here. I’ll be right back.

238
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:13,080
August.

239
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,960
Don’t you think that your shirt color
will hurt other people’s eyes?

240
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:18,320
I was going to warn you
when we were at home.

241
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,200
You are so lame.

242
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:22,840
Don’t you know this is Y2K style?

243
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,920
I thought you wanted to be
a motorbike taxi rider.

244
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:29,240
Are you afraid people won’t know
that you’re a basketball athlete?

245
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,320
Why don’t you carry a ball too

246
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,600
You look like a fake basketballer.

247
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,360
This is my style. Don’t look down on me.

248
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,520
You look like a motorbike taxi rider.

249
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,000
Where is your motorbike?

250
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,400
That’s enough. Stop bickering.

251
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:42,760
Ko Song, why did you stop them?

252
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,040
It’s getting fun.

253
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:48,920
Your outfit.

254
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:53,440
I think you should do this.

255
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,160
It’s okay. I can do it myself.

256
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:07,160
It’s okay.

257
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:09,560
It’s okay.

258
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:22,560
This is it.

259
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,120
You look great.

260
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,000
Where is Achi?

261
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:31,320
How would I know? I’m standing with you.

262
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,440
Yes, Boss Ko

263
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:39,640
Damn.

264
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,120
Wicked.

265
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,600
It looks so cool.

266
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:46,440
Are you ready?

267
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:48,480
I’m ready since I was born.

268
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,840
Let’s go.

269
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,720
Let’s go.

270
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,360
Let’s go.

271
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:19,240
We arrived.

272
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:21,560
I want the ride to be a bit longer.

273
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,520
Uncle, can you take us on a ride?

274
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:28,520
He’s acting cool.

275
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,320
I saw you dancing to Ricky Martin’s song.

276
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,760
You are getting overexcited.

277
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:36,240
You are living in a beach town,
but you act like you never saw the sea.

278
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,040
Augar, why do you have to ruin the mood?

279
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,360
When will we get to ride on a Wolk again?

280
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,200
Idiot, it’s called Volkswagen.

281
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,120
It sounds the same.

282
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:43,800
Idiot.

283
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:50,120
Let’s put our bags inside.

284
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:50,680
Sure.

285
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:52,640
Come on.

286
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,600
Are you that happy?

287
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:02,960
I’m happy
because we came on this trip together.

288
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,680
Can you two stop flirting?

289
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,680
Let’s take the bags inside and go to the beach.

290
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,320
I want to kick your butt, August.

291
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:11,760
I’ll show you the bedroom.

292
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:18,320
Hua Hin, here I come.

293
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,560
Augar, you’ve got to become an athlete.

294
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:43,000
Of course.

295
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:45,040
Go, go. Augar, Go.

296
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:45,920
Don’t push me.

297
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,040
Augar wins.

298
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:58,960
Guys.

299
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:01,440
Achi’s chauffeur is over there.

300
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,480
Should I pretend to get cramps?

301
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:08,840
Good idea, Achi.

302
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,560
Please help us.

303
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:17,680
Achi is having cramps.

304
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:22,400
This way. Hurry up.

305
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:29,360
Don’t splash me.

306
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,200
Stop it.

307
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,360
No.

308
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:45,960
Uncle.

309
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,680
♪ Every time that we meet again ♪

310
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:08,600
♪ Something grows a little more each day ♪

311
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:13,280
♪ The closer we are,
the more I feel the love I’ve waited for ♪

312
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:16,480
♪ Might not be too far away at all ♪

313
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:20,480
♪ Even when winter fades I’ll still wait on ♪

314
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:24,480
♪ Till the final raindrop falls,
hope is never gone ♪

315
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:28,840
♪ As long as I have you holding my hand
as we walk on ♪

316
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:47,600
♪ I fear nothing if this season has you ♪

317
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:55,600
Aren’t you feeling hot?

318
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:00,160
No, it’s breezy here.

319
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:05,600
We should go inside.

320
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:07,480
You are wet. You may get sick.

321
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,720
Later.

322
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:15,040
Fine.

323
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,840
This reminds me of the first time
we went to the beach together.

324
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,480
It was dark then.

325
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,520
We only saw lights from the boats.

326
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:36,080
But right now, it’s bright,
and the view is wide-open.

327
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:45,800
Close your eyes.

328
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,440
Time flies so fast.

329
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,840
Soon it will be our last year in high school.

330
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:29,880
Time really flies.

331
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:35,720
I don’t like it.

332
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:39,840
Why?

333
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:43,280
I don’t know.

334
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,800
I have this sinking feeling.

335
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:53,720
So…

336
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,720
What are you going to do after graduation

337
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:05,480
I have never thought about that.

338
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:07,480
What about you?

339
00:25:13,560 --> 00:25:14,640
I’d probably study in a med school.

340
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:22,360
Then I should attend the same school as you.

341
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,400
A med school?

342
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:28,120
Why?

343
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,080
Do you think I can’t attend a med school?

344
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:37,720
Aren’t you afraid?

345
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,560
If you are a med student,
you have to study with a dead body.

346
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:45,120
You have to stay in a hospital at night.

347
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:48,040
It’s dark and silent.

348
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:52,040
Then…

349
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,120
can I study as a patient?

350
00:25:54,880 --> 00:26:00,480
At least, I would be under
the care of Dr. Kanin Siritara.

351
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,080
Nonsense.

352
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:12,600
Come on, it’s getting cold. Let’s go inside.

353
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,760
Why are you patting on my butt?

354
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,400
It’s covered with sand.

355
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,320
Don’t pat on my butt.

356
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,560
But it’s covered with sand.

357
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:34,880
Don’t pat on my butt.

358
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:39,560
Ko Neung. Ko Song.

359
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,400
Ko Neung. Ko Song.

360
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:43,040
We have a problem.

361
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:44,760
What is the problem?

362
00:26:56,840 --> 00:26:57,720
The house is big.

363
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,040
But we have to take a shower outside.

364
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:00,600
Right.

365
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,160
Why does the bathroom
have to be broken now?

366
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:03,520
I’m cold.

367
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:14,120
Ko Song.

368
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:15,920
It will splash on my face.

369
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,080
It won’t.

370
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:18,760
Shampoo shouldn’t touch our face.

371
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:21,080
Water.

372
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:22,640
What?

373
00:27:22,760 --> 00:27:23,480
It gets in my eyes.

374
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:25,240
It gets in your eyes?

375
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,840
I’ll help you. Wait a sec.

376
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:29,120
I’ll wash my hands first.

377
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,560
Hurry up. It gets in my eyes.

378
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,360
Stay still.

379
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:42,160
You look like Son Goku from Super Saiyan.

380
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,640
What does he look like?

381
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:17,720
What?

382
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:19,680
Is it better?

383
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:22,320
Yes.

384
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:23,800
Ouch.

385
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:24,680
Ko Song.

386
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:25,800
It got into my mouth.

387
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:26,440
Ko.

388
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:27,960
Ko.

389
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:29,000
Give it to me.

390
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:29,440
Ko.

391
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,120
Charge in!

392
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,320
It gets in my eyes.

393
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,640
Put your hair down.

394
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:52,080
Nasal irrigation.

395
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:00,680
Ko.

396
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,160
Damn, this is powder.

397
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:17,120
August.

398
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:18,680
Do you know how to grill meat

399
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,320
Of course.

400
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:23,480
My grilling skills are guaranteed.
I got an A for boy scout class.

401
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,240
His words sound scary.

402
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:28,080
I want to taste the food that August cooks.

403
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:29,040
I’m a better cook than him.

404
00:29:29,720 --> 00:29:30,280
Really?

405
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:32,560
Then I’ll eat it a lot.

406
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:35,760
Yes, you need to eat a lot
because you are so small.

407
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,280
Small like this?

408
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,040
Small like this.

409
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:41,200
What are Ko Neung and Ko Song doing?

410
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:44,160
They probably complain
while taking a shower.

411
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:49,800
You two can’t tell them
that I broke the faucet.

412
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,240
Otherwise, I’ll hit you

413
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,440
Fine, brother.

414
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,400
I won’t tell them.

415
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:56,520
I’m back.

416
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:00,680
Is he smiling?

417
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,160
I’m as surprised as you.

418
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,480
When we rode the banana boat,
his face was expressionless.

419
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:06,240
I think he feels comfortable with us now.

420
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:09,040
I’ll let you guys cook.

421
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:10,360
Thank you.

422
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:12,160
What do we have for dinner?

423
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,120
Will we finish it all?

424
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:22,360
Uncle, please join us for dinner.

425
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,600
I need to get a plumber to fix the faucet.

426
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:26,440
You need to lift the handle
to turn on the faucet.

427
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:28,960
But you turn the handle so hard
that it’s broken, Augar.

428
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,520
I’ve got to go.

429
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:36,040
I…

430
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:36,640
Augar!

431
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:37,520
Augar!

432
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:41,520
Uncle barely says anything,
but when he starts to talk, he talks a lot.

433
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:42,520
Ko Song, catch him.

434
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:45,440
I won’t let you get away, Augar.

435
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:47,680
Where are you going?

436
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:48,800
August, why are you helping them?

437
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,120
Take off his clothes.

438
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:06,760
When you grill meat,
don’t flip it too often.

439
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:09,320
Here is freshly cooked rice.

440
00:31:15,680 --> 00:31:16,240
Hey.

441
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:17,560
Ko Song.

442
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,240
Who taught you to cut pork like that?

443
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:21,120
You’re clueless.

444
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:23,400
Cut it like this. Get it?

445
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:24,480
Try it.

446
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:29,560
Do you finish washing the vegetables?

447
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:30,200
Yes.

448
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:31,800
Let’s go.

449
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:35,040
Wash it again.

450
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,600
Augar, why did you rush me?

451
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:38,840
Don’t splash the water.

452
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,840
I think I would get to eat your finger too.

453
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,520
Be careful.

454
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:52,040
He must be hungry.

455
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:54,680
He’s eating without saying a word.

456
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,640
Why doesn’t Uncle join us for dinner?

457
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:01,000
He said he has to check the plumber’s work.

458
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:02,360
The plumber might be sloppy.

459
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:03,640
He will eat later.

460
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:05,440
We should save some food for him.

461
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:07,080
He’s doing a lot for us.

462
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:10,080
August.

463
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:11,840
Your friend has grown up

464
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,680
Now, he thinks about other people.

465
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:16,480
In the past, he ate everything
without thinking about anyone.

466
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:18,680
Boss Ko has grown up.

467
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:21,040
We need to celebrate.

468
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:25,560
Yay!

469
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:27,440
Are you having fun?

470
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:29,200
I’ll poke you.

471
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:32,440
Why can’t I become more mature?

472
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:35,640
You can, but I’m not used to it.

473
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:36,920
Ko Song.

474
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:38,760
Do you want to get smacked?

475
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:41,120
Do you want to try me?

476
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,240
Why did you take the photo
without telling me?

477
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:48,280
I want to have proof
that you became a better person.

478
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:49,800
Damn, you guys.

479
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:51,680
You gang up on me.

480
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,640
It’s good that you want to improve yourself.

481
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:57,480
It will help you find your goal.

482
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:02,560
I’m curious
what our lives will be like in the future.

483
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:06,560
I told you I wanted to be an expert on manga.

484
00:33:07,280 --> 00:33:08,240
Now, I've grown up.

485
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,400
I have so many questions

486
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,160
What are they?

487
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:16,920
Do I really like it?

488
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:22,520
Won’t people think my dream is nonsense?

489
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:27,680
You don’t need to care
what they think about your dream.

490
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:30,400
It’s good that you respect your dream.

491
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:37,920
People see me as a smart student
who gets good grades.

492
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:42,600
When my parents ask me
what I want to do in life, I can’t answer them.

493
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:48,080
Will adult life be as stressful
as many adults say?

494
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:52,120
When we were young,
we wanted to be an adult.

495
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,680
But now, it’s scary to be an adult.

496
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,080
It’s hard to say.

497
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:01,720
Augar, you are the only one
who doesn’t have this problem.

498
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:08,600
You know what?

499
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,320
I’m not even sure
if I really want to be a basketball player.

500
00:34:13,120 --> 00:34:15,520
Basketball is something
my dad has been teaching me.

501
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:17,920
It’s just something I’m growing up with.

502
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,200
To be honest,

503
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,160
I’m suck at studying.

504
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:25,000
If I don’t work hard on playing basketball,
I would have nothing I’m good at.

505
00:34:25,720 --> 00:34:29,720
It’s normal to not know what you want to do.

506
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,200
But I already chose my path.

507
00:34:32,640 --> 00:34:33,960
Don’t you think it’s scarier?

508
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:40,560
Don’t you think it’s scarier?

509
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,080
What?

510
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:47,240
The one who started this serious topic
is Achi again.

511
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:49,920
That’s right.

512
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:50,920
You again, Achi.

513
00:34:51,120 --> 00:34:52,720
This is so you.

514
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:55,440
Let’s forget it and dig in.

515
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:59,880
Dig in.

516
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:02,480
An army marches on its stomach.

517
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:05,400
We are so unlucky.

518
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,640
We spin the bottle and end up on dish duty.

519
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:10,280
Luckily, it’s you.

520
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:11,640
If I did it with August,

521
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:13,560
we would be fighting
and end up breaking a dish.

522
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:18,360
I thought you wanted to do it with me.

523
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,000
Are you sulking?

524
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:25,240
Augar, my hair is now wet.

525
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:26,000
Sorry.

526
00:35:29,520 --> 00:35:31,240
I think you really love basketball.

527
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:33,040
How did you know that?

528
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:36,840
We’ve known each other for two years.

529
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:40,240
I see that look in your eyes
when you play basketball.

530
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:42,480
What look?

531
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:47,520
You look determined and full of happiness.

532
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:51,000
Why do you know me so well?

533
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:52,280
Because I’ve been watching you.

534
00:35:56,720 --> 00:35:57,920
You’ve been watching me?

535
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:04,040
Yes.

536
00:36:06,080 --> 00:36:07,120
Since when?

537
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:11,160
I don’t remember.

538
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:22,000
Can you tell what I’m thinking right now?

539
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:27,280
Augar.

540
00:36:30,360 --> 00:36:31,360
You’re getting too close.

541
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:35,520
So you can see what I’m feeling.

542
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:38,360
Augar, stop teasing me.

543
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:42,800
Okay, I’ll stop teasing you.

544
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:08,320
Why are you patting on my butt?

545
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:10,120
(Maybe what my mom said is true.)

546
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:23,920
(Why did I get so shy when he did that?)

547
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:30,400
(Am I…)

548
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:34,080
(…falling for him?)

549
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:41,040
(Didn’t you say you wanted us
to go back to being friends?

550
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,480
(Why are you sending me mixed signals?)

551
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:50,680
(If this gets stronger,)

552
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:52,800
(will I be able to hold it back?)

553
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:34,720
Guys.

554
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,920
Let’s write a postcard.

555
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:39,360
Sure.

556
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:41,480
When did you become a romantic guy?

557
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:43,360
What?

558
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:46,000
I haven’t said whom I will write it to.

559
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,200
You don’t need to say it, but I already knew

560
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,400
What?

561
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:55,200
Let’s pick a postcard.

562
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:57,720
You can write to whoever you want.

563
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:05,560
August, what are you writing?

564
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,400
Augar, it has to be a secret.

565
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:38,000
Let’s go back to the van.

566
00:40:58,040 --> 00:40:59,280
Where did you go last night?

567
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:16,440
It’s so quiet that we can hear the wind

568
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:18,680
Yes.

569
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:28,320
Do you think…

570
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:31,280
the stars we see here look the same
as when we watch them at home?

571
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:38,480
Theoretically, they are barely different.

572
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:39,920
We almost can’t tell the difference.

573
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:44,480
Do you know the name of the stars?

574
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:48,240
I don’t know everything, Orange.

575
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:49,760
I don’t know their names.

576
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:51,200
But I know.

577
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:55,280
Do you see the star that is over there alone?

578
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:56,720
Yes.

579
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,120
That’s August.

580
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:02,680
Because it likes being alone.

581
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:08,040
Here.

582
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:10,360
These are the Augar constellation.

583
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:14,800
They stick together
and look like a basketball ball.

584
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:18,720
Where is Achi’s star?

585
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:25,160
Let’s say every star in the sky is his.

586
00:42:26,720 --> 00:42:28,200
Because he’s rich.

587
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:30,400
He can own all of them.

588
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,840
Then there’s no star left for us.

589
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:45,320
There’s no star for me.

590
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,680
I’m not good enough to be a star.

591
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:53,640
There.

592
00:42:54,520 --> 00:42:56,840
That one is yours, the biggest one.

593
00:43:00,120 --> 00:43:01,480
But that’s the moon.

594
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:04,240
For me,

595
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:06,880
the moon is you, Ko Song.

596
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:21,640
When I turn off the light in my room,
a light slowly shines through my window.

597
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:23,680
I see you every night before I fall asleep.

598
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:28,560
When I have a problem,

599
00:43:30,280 --> 00:43:31,880
you are always my light.

600
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:36,280
My life without you,

601
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:40,920
it is so dull.

602
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:46,520
I…

603
00:43:47,280 --> 00:43:48,440
That’s how I really feel.

604
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:28,360
♪ “I love you” I never said ♪

605
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:33,480
♪ I kept them, thinking you felt the same ♪

606
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:36,360
♪ But you left without a word ♪

607
00:44:36,360 --> 00:44:40,720
♪ Kept thinking, if I’d said them first ♪

608
00:44:40,720 --> 00:44:43,600
♪ Things might've turned out better ♪

609
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:53,640
♪ Distance only makes me think it over ♪

610
00:44:53,640 --> 00:45:02,680
♪ What should be said
if we again meet each other ♪

611
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:05,520
I mean it this time.

612
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:38,560
Are you crossing the line?

613
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:44,280
You crossed it first last night.

614
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:48,040
♪ Will say "I love you" ♪

615
00:45:49,320 --> 00:45:53,480
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

616
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:53,920
(Don’t look at me with those eyes.)

617
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,200
♪ No more watching from afar,
letting chances go ♪
(Don’t look at me with those eyes.)

618
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:58,400
♪ No more watching from afar,
letting chances go ♪

619
00:45:58,400 --> 00:46:00,040
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

620
00:46:00,040 --> 00:46:01,360
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪
(Let me mess up your hair, little boy.)

621
00:46:01,360 --> 00:46:05,400
♪ To make this worth the wait after all ♪
(Let me mess up your hair, little boy.)

622
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:09,520
(I suddenly think of you.
I wish you were here.)

623
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:17,160
(Thank you for coming into my life
and bringing light to it.)

624
00:46:24,400 --> 00:46:26,080
(You don’t need to be a star.)

625
00:46:29,320 --> 00:46:30,920
(You can be my sun.)

626
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:36,960
♪ To make this worth the wait after all ♪

627
00:46:41,040 --> 00:46:43,520
- So we are dating, right?

628
00:46:46,160 --> 00:46:48,920
- Please join the group of the faculty
you want to study in.

629
00:46:49,080 --> 00:46:52,200
- So Tle is also choosing
to attend a med school like Ko Song.

630
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:53,840
- I think so.

631
00:46:53,960 --> 00:46:55,480
- Don’t you worry about being apart from him?

632
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:02,240
- Ko Song, after we graduate from school,
will you leave me?

633
00:47:07,520 --> 00:47:08,280
- It’s okay.

634
00:47:09,040 --> 00:47:10,520
- I promise that we will see each other.

